snippets.title: CatalogService getIamPolicy Sample
snippets.description: Gets the access control policy for a contentitem resource. A `NOT_FOUND` error is returned if the resource does not exist. An empty policy is returned if the resource exists but does not have a policy set on it. Caller must have Google IAM `dataplex.content.getIamPolicy` permission on the resource.

snippets.title: CatalogService setIamPolicy Sample
snippets.description: Sets the access control policy on the specified contentitem resource. Replaces any existing policy. Caller must have Google IAM `dataplex.content.setIamPolicy` permission on the resource.

snippets.title: CatalogService testIamPermissions Sample
snippets.description: Returns the caller's permissions on a resource. If the resource does not exist, an empty set of permissions is returned (a `NOT_FOUND` error is not returned). A caller is not required to have Google IAM permission to make this request. Note: This operation is designed to be used for building permission-aware UIs and command-line tools, not for authorization checking. This operation may "fail open" without warning.
